This paper deals with image translation using deep learning methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses disentangling internal representations, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) is also a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these four categories are the most likely. Other possible categories could include computer systems and networking (cs.SY) if the paper discusses any hardware or system-level optimizations, or human-computer interaction (cs.HC) if the paper discusses any user studies or evaluations. However, these categories are less likely given the focus of the paper on image translation and disentanglement.
